name: The Common Cup
directions: Right on the corner of Morse and Greenview.  Bathrooms are toward the back.
comment: The people here are really cool and you can just walk in and use the bathroom.  There is one bathroom directly to the back and another to the right down the hall.  Both are single stall non-gendered.

name: Subway
directions: Right toward the back.  One single stall non-gendered.
comment: There is a sign that says purchase is necessary to use the bathroom.

name: Sister's of the Road Cafe
directions: It is a tight fit through the cafe so it is not really accessible. The bathrooms are located at the back of the cafe. There are two gender neutral, locking single bathrooms. This is a safe space business. I know gender variant folks work there and you will be respected.
comment: The Cafe is open Monday through Friday. This is what they have to say about the cafe, \"Our Portland, Oregon nonprofit cafe is the heart and flagship of our organization. We are open to everyone.  We serve low cost, hot, nutritious meals that can be purchased in a variety of ways, including with cash, food stamps, or in exchange for work.\"

name: Target Cascade Station
directions: When you walk into the store the bathrooms are on your right before customer service. There is a single room family bathroom that is accessible.
comment: I think we should all boycott Target but if you're going then it's good to know that this location has a safe place to pee.

name: Bump N Grind Cafe
directions: all main floor, street access
comment: open mon-sun 8am-6pm; chill atmosphere, queer and trans friendly

name: Katherine Legge Memorial Park, Hinsdale IL
street: Katherine Leggee Park, beteween 57th and plainfield on county line road
directions: Drive in entrance, bathrooms in small building behind lodge, other port-potties located throughout park with a handi-accessable porta-pottie too.
comment: Handicapped portapottie is really nice.

name: palmer house hilton
directions: Main lobby to the right of the front desk.
comment: Not accessible after 10pm. Stall door from floor to top of stall. Known cop bathroom.

name: Giant Foods
directions: When you walk in, walk along the front of the store in front of the cash registers and check out lines heading left. The bathrooms will be on the left before the bakery and frozen foods.

name: Fordham Law School library
directions: Library stack 6 by the elevator.
comment: Library hours are usually 8 am - midnight.  If you can get in the building, you can use it.  Bathroom is single stall, locking, by the elevator, and has a wide door and accessibility rails.  There is another gender-neutral bathroom at Fordham Law on the 4th floor but it is marked Faculty/Staff and not always open.

name: I-89 rest area between Exit 12 & Exit 13
directions: Exterior access bathrooms, single lockable doors
comment: The sign requests that you only use after hours, when the building is closed, but they're open 24 hours, and the inside bathrooms could not be more gendered.

name: Jones Hall
directions: First floor, to the right of the elevators.

name: Portland State University Smith Hall Mezanine
directions: go up small stairs behind info desk from Broadway street door, turn left at top of stairs
comment: there has been concern about IV drug use in these stalls, as well as houseless community members using them for shelter (which raises lots of other questions, such as WTF is Portland doing about homelessness (answer, nothing))

name: Chandler Fashion Center
directions: Just west of the food court.
comment: This is a family restroom, but unlike Arizona Mills, anyone can use it.

name: YMCA
directions: first floor, down the hallway towards men's locker room, on the right. It is a family restrom.
comment: ask the front desk attendant if you  may use the restroom. They don't care which one you use. Only reason to ask is if you aren't a member, you can't just stroll past the front desk. Never had any problems. door locks securely.

name: Orlando Fasion Square Mall
directions: Go all the way to the end with the theater and the food court. This bathroom is in the theater and is a family restroom.
comment: I walk up to the ticket collector, and ask if I may use their restroom. I've had no hassles. If they decline you, mention you are between genders, and are not able to use the other bathrooms. Usually the female ticket collector in the afternoons is nice and 100% no hassle. locks securely

name: Starbucks
directions: Past the serving counter and the seats. both single occupancy.
comment: secure locking doors, Used several times, no problems.

name: Subway
directions: Off to the side of the tables and counter are the two single occupancy bathrooms.
comment: locks securely, I've used twice now, no problems.

name: Grendel\\
directions: Near the entrance.The signs are labelled\"Either\" and \"Or.\"

name: Bedford Farms Ice Cream
directions: As you walk in the store, there will be an exit sign in the back on the right. That door is directly opposite the bathroom, near the freezers.

name: Pantry Kitchen
directions: At the back of the restaraunt, two single bathrooms with locking doors in a hallway.
comment: GREAT place to eat! try the raisin bread pudding. seriously.

name: Café Jean-Sébastien Bar & Tapas
directions: Main Floor

name: Walmart
directions: Way in the back of the store by electronics. Its a \"family\" bathroom, but anyone can use it.
comment: Seriously should be cleaned more than once a day, but when your desperate....

name: Drift's House
directions: I noticed that there aren't any listings of safe bathrooms east of 82nd in Portland. Well I just happen to live further out from the city hub and wanted to post this in case anyone ever needed the info. I live in apartment #3 of a split house. My door is through the front yard gate around the left of the house and down the stairs.
comment: If you've got to use the bathroom give me a call (503)278-2726. My name is Drift

name: Sushi Ichiban (formerly Takahashi)
directions: At the back of the restaurant there is a small hallway that leads to the gendered single stall bathrooms.
comment: I love their sushi and there are awesome folks that work there. Try the yummy vegan sushi.

name: Bipartisan Cafe
directions: When you walk inside the cafe there are two gender neutral bathrooms at the back of the cafe. One has a picture of an elephant on the door and the other has a picture of a donkey.
comment: Mon-Fri 6:30am-10pmSaturday 7am-10pmSunday 7am-9pmAlso they make a lot of delicious food. I specifically go there for the homemade pies.

name: Reves Center
directions: Two right next to each other on second floor (one floor up from the ground floor, may actually be called third floor)
comment: This building is a darn maze with lots of dead ends, but it's small, so you should be able to find them.

name: McDonald's (and Chipotle Mexican Grill)
directions: The bathroom is between the Chipotle and the McDonald's in an joined space.

name: Burger King
directions: Walk in either door and walk down the stairs to the downstairs area. The bathrooms, from the stairs, are on the left side.

name: Ballantine Hall
directions: On the ground (not first) floor, by the giant globe.Floor 5, across from 548 (not accessible, all gender)Floor 4, across 402 (accessible, all gender)Floor 1, across from 105 (accessible, all gender)
comment: single stall locking gender neutral / disabled bathroom.

name: Willkie Center Building
directions: enter the center building, head left. between the c-store and the library.
comment: designated gender-neutral bathroom. single stall that locks. the building closes at midnight.

name: Side Street Inn - Kapahulu
directions: In the hallway in front of the entrance to Side Street Inn (located in the Prudential Building).
comment: You can probably sneak in from outside without being a patron of the Side Street Inn as the bathrooms are in the hallway outside of the restaurant.  There's two multi-stall gendered restrooms on either side of a single stall, disabled-accessible, unisex restroom. Hours: 3pm-12am, 7 days a week.

name: TF Green Airport
directions: there are two gender-neutral/family/wheelchair-accessible bathrooms within the security area of the airport, one in each of the two concourses, between the entrances to the mens & womens bathrooms. follow the signs!
comment: once you're in the airport... it's free to use the bathrooms. hopefully \"restricted\" is the right category to put this under...

name: Joe Van Gogh
directions: bathroom at back
comment: mon - fri : 6:30am to 9:00pmsat : 7:00am to 9:00pmsun : 8:00am to 6:00pm

name: Ben and Jerry's Ice Cream
directions: To the right of the front door. Closest door to the window. No sign marking it.
comment: VERY LGBT friendly.

name: Hello Cupcake
directions: Go straight ahead from the door in a small out-cove in the back.
comment: Smell are amazing! Offer vegan cupcakes too!

name: Smoothie King
directions: Straight back past the ordering counter in the back left of the seating area.

name: Five Guys Burgers and Fried
directions: Straight back! Doors on the left

name: Sweet Green
directions: Go straight back past the ordering counter in to a small hallway. Doors are on the left.

name: Tynan Coffee and Tea
directions: The bathrooms are in the back right corner if you're standing at the front door.
comment: Very cute and trendy!

name: Ox & Rabbit Soda & Sundries
directions: at back of store
comment: Mon-Sat 12pm-8pm; Sun 12pm-5pm

name: FedEx Office
directions: You need to get a key from the people at the counter. Restoom is behind the printing center.
comment: Open 24 hours.

name: Metro 8 Steakhouse
directions: There are 2 unisex restrooms, one just past the bar and one around the corner at the back of the building.
comment: Open daily 5pm - 11:30pm.

name: Bean Traders Coffee
directions: downstairs at back of building

name: Devil's Pizzeria
directions: in back of restaurant
comment: Monday through Wednesday - 11:00 AM to 12:00 AMThursday, Friday and Saturday - 11:00 AM to 3:00 AMClosed on Sundays

name: Francesca's
directions: There are 2 restrooms in the hallway behind the counter. There is another one that may be available in the other room against the wall.
comment: Open Mon-Thu 11am-11pm; Fri-Sat 11am-12am; Sun 11am-10pmVery queer-friendly!

name: Back to the Grind
directions: NNW corner of the big main room
comment: Queer hang-out.  The single-stall restrooms are gendered, but people often ignore the signs.  Good coffee too.

name: My Other Brother Darrell's
directions: main floor after the bar, before the kitchen

name: Times Supermarket
directions: Back of the store, near beer/liquor.
comment: 6-10pm daily.  Single-stalled, disabled-accessible locking bathroom with toilet and urinal.

name: Monroe Library
directions: Walk in the front door. Take a right when you walk in through the theft detectors, take a left before you get to the computer area.
comment: Open almost every day from 6 am to 2am, weekend hours vary. Be careful though, my friend (a cis-male) needed to use the restroom and the men\\'s was occupied, so he used the women\\'s marked one. A maintenance lady saw him exit and a huge ordeal occurred at the school.

name: La Davina
directions: Located in the bottom floor of Carrollton Hall, the door is in the turnabout. Walk straight in and it's to the right of the register.

name: Westfield Washington Public Library
directions: Ask at the desk for directions
comment: Hours of OperationMonday 10:00 - 8:00Tuesday 10:00 - 8:00Wednesday 10:00 - 8:00Thursday 10:00 - 8:00Friday 10:00 - 6:00Saturday 10:00 - 5:00Sunday Closed

name: Don's Liquor Mart
directions: Toward the left as you walk in, way at the back of the store in the corner.
comment: Single stall, unisex.

name: Tuvalu coffee house
directions: In back on left

name: Minneapolis College of Art and Design
directions: Morrison building, by the library
comment: Normal business hours if not a student, though after hours you can sign in with security guard at other entrance and walk across skyway.

name: Terminal 5
directions: On the roof. It's not labeled, but it's the line of doors near the red lights.
comment: People with visual sensitivity might want to avoid these, as inside the stalls they use blacklights instead of regular lights.

name: Remedy
directions: Towards the back of the diner
comment: Stalls are fairly small

name: George's Ice Cream and Sweets
directions: walk to the back, several doors
comment: Sun-Thu 11am-10pmFri&Sat 11am-11pm

name: Coffee Chicago
directions: Look for the phone sign just past the counter.
comment: M-F 7a-9pSat 3a-9pSun 9a-8p

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: From the 7th street entrance, head back past the ordering counter in the corner on the right. From the H street entrance, it's very close just to the left and better for sneaking in, but there are steps.

name: Dunkin' Donuts
directions: Walk in the door on the right of the counter in the back. Make SURE you buy something.

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: Walk in an head straight back on your right.

name: Northgate Mall Food Court
directions: Food Court. 2 single stall \"Family Restrooms\" in the food court where the mall security office(ha)and public telephones are located. on the opposite side as the mass gendered bathrooms.
comment: Mon-Sat 10am-9pm. Sun 12pm-6pm.Also has a rocking chair for nursing mothers and a changing table. Sheriffs will hassle genderqueer ppl who go into gendered bathrooms. Don't miss the carousel!

name: Pollo Sabroso
directions: Walk in the front door and head straight back!

name: Uptowner Cafe
directions: Walk in and head straight to the back towards the back right corner.

name: Subway Sandwiches
directions: Walk in the door, order your food, then head straight back and it's the door on your right.

name: Sticky Fingers Bakery
directions: Walk in the front door and look to your left!
comment: This bakery is also very vegan friendly!

name: Moe's Southwest Grill
directions: back past the booths and the food line. Single occupency, doors lock securely. I've had zero problems there.
comment: I don't remember the hours they are open but here is the phone number so you can call and ask: (407) 671-3566‰Û_

name: East Bay Meditation Center
comment: wednesdays meditation for us

name: Memorial City Mall
directions: Restroom is located near the carousel (south entrance)
comment: HoursMon-Sat: 10am-9pmSun: 12pm-6pm
